WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:04.003
(Silence)

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:16.084 --> 00:17.685
(Crickets)

00:21.455 --> 00:22.523
Hear anything?

00:22.556 --> 00:23.791
Nope.

00:27.528 --> 00:28.362
Bev?

00:28.396 --> 00:30.164
Nope.

00:30.198 --> 00:32.100
This thing's stupid.

00:32.566 --> 00:34.202
You know what isn't stupid?

00:34.235 --> 00:36.604
Your birthday present.

00:39.473 --> 00:41.075
What is it?

00:41.109 --> 00:42.643
Just open it.

00:46.214 --> 00:49.283
I can't believe you stole
this from your dad's office.

00:49.317 --> 00:51.719
Let's try it.

00:55.289 --> 00:56.724
Is this Jewish?

00:56.757 --> 00:58.392
You mean Hebrew?

00:58.426 --> 00:59.727
Right, Yossi?

00:59.760 --> 01:01.462
Yeah, but it's not Hebrew.

01:01.495 --> 01:04.098
I think it's Chinese.

01:04.132 --> 01:05.399
How does this thing work?

01:05.433 --> 01:07.168
Well, it's a spirit board.

01:07.201 --> 01:09.803
You're supposed to contact
people or ask it questions.

01:09.837 --> 01:12.140
Like dead people?

01:12.173 --> 01:14.808
Or is Bev going to kiss you?

01:15.309 --> 01:16.777
Shut up, Max.

01:16.810 --> 01:17.711
What?

01:17.745 --> 01:19.880
I'm just stating the obvious.

01:19.913 --> 01:22.416
I think just dead people.

01:23.184 --> 01:25.419
Ask it a question already.

01:26.420 --> 01:30.258
Did my mom and dad get me
the BMX bike that I wanted?

01:46.340 --> 01:49.177
Does Beverly Morgan like Yossi?

01:54.448 --> 01:56.317
This thing is also stupid.

01:56.350 --> 01:57.485
Maybe because
you're not asking it

01:57.518 --> 01:59.387
The right questions.

02:00.454 --> 02:02.323
Hey, Bev.

02:02.356 --> 02:03.857
Your parents are here.

02:03.891 --> 02:05.626
- Oh, okay.
- And you two?

02:05.659 --> 02:07.195
It's time to get to sleep.

02:07.228 --> 02:08.196
Alright, I promised
your dad that you

02:08.229 --> 02:09.497
Would be in bed
before nine, pal.

02:09.530 --> 02:10.431
Alright boys?

02:10.464 --> 02:11.332
Okay, Dad.

02:11.365 --> 02:12.266
Okay, Mr. T.

02:12.300 --> 02:13.834
Alrighty.

02:15.536 --> 02:17.671
You know, I
think Max asked one

02:17.705 --> 02:19.507
Right question on the board?

02:19.540 --> 02:22.176
Which one?

02:25.213 --> 02:26.580
Gross!

02:27.548 --> 02:29.617
You going to miss me?

02:29.650 --> 02:31.552
Always.

02:34.655 --> 02:37.425
Okay, Romeo,
let's get to bed.

02:47.535 --> 02:49.837
(Scary music)

03:04.252 --> 03:06.554
(Heavy breathing)

03:06.587 --> 03:08.456
Quit it, Max.

03:32.380 --> 03:34.648
Max, is that you?

03:44.492 --> 03:46.294
(Yelling)

03:47.661 --> 03:50.331
(Telephone)

03:54.602 --> 03:56.437
Hello?

03:57.771 --> 03:59.307
Hello?

03:59.340 --> 04:00.374
Aba?

04:00.408 --> 04:03.311
Yossi! Are you
okay? What happened?

04:03.344 --> 04:06.380
It's Max, something's wrong.

04:07.415 --> 04:09.383
Yosef.

04:09.417 --> 04:12.453
I took the Ouija board
and let Max play with it and

04:12.486 --> 04:13.554
What Ouija board?

04:13.587 --> 04:15.389
The one from my office?

04:15.423 --> 04:17.458
Yes, I'm sorry, I...

04:17.491 --> 04:19.360
It's out.

04:20.528 --> 04:23.297
Yosef, you find a
place to hide at Max's

04:23.331 --> 04:25.366
And you don't come
out 'til I get you!

04:25.799 --> 04:28.869
Yosef! Yosef!

04:40.481 --> 04:43.283
(Scary music)

05:21.855 --> 05:24.458
Show yourself demon!

07:00.788 --> 07:03.423
Yousef?

07:59.613 --> 08:02.516
Mark?

08:05.686 --> 08:07.621
Aba?

08:12.593 --> 08:15.563
Yousef, run!

08:23.871 --> 08:26.106
Hello?

08:28.776 --> 08:30.711
Oh.

08:31.679 --> 08:33.513
Yeah.

08:34.582 --> 08:37.183
Yeah, I'll be there
as soon as I can.

08:37.918 --> 08:39.753
Bye.

08:51.632 --> 08:53.166
I'm so glad I finally
get to meet my grandfather

08:53.200 --> 08:54.702
For the first time,

08:54.735 --> 08:57.270
Right before he's about to die.

08:58.305 --> 09:00.073
Yeah, I guess I deserve that.

09:00.107 --> 09:01.709
You think?

09:01.742 --> 09:06.313
Look, you want to blame Dov
for keeping us apart, not me.

09:06.914 --> 09:08.649
Why do you always
call him that?

09:08.682 --> 09:09.583
Because that's his name.

09:09.617 --> 09:10.718
I know, but he's your father.

09:10.751 --> 09:13.020
Was my father.

09:13.053 --> 09:15.623
I haven't seen that
man in over 30 years.

09:18.759 --> 09:20.661
I'm having a hard
time figuring out

09:20.694 --> 09:22.095
Why he would put
you in a foster home

09:22.129 --> 09:23.631
For no reason.

09:23.664 --> 09:24.732
Because your grandfather is an

09:24.765 --> 09:26.366
Extremely selfish man.

09:26.399 --> 09:28.669
Just sucks is all.

09:28.702 --> 09:29.637
Especially considering
you can't remember

09:29.670 --> 09:33.240
Your childhood because
of some stupid accident.

09:33.807 --> 09:35.275
Yeah.

09:35.308 --> 09:37.745
It does suck.

09:37.778 --> 09:40.280
But I had no control over that.

09:40.781 --> 09:41.749
But you know the
one thing I do have

09:41.782 --> 09:44.685
Control over is
being your father.

09:44.718 --> 09:46.119
And just so you
know, I would never

09:46.153 --> 09:49.923
Ever do what Dov
did to me to you.

09:49.957 --> 09:52.693
I care about you way too much.

09:53.426 --> 09:56.263
I care about you too, Dad.

10:35.836 --> 10:37.738
Come on, Dad.

10:45.178 --> 10:47.080
(Doorbell)

11:26.787 --> 11:28.722
He's stable now.

11:28.756 --> 11:31.391
But we're not sure
how much time he has.

11:31.424 --> 11:34.061
Does he know we're here?

11:34.094 --> 11:37.430
No. I did has you asked.

11:37.464 --> 11:40.333
I didn't tell him
you were coming.

11:40.367 --> 11:42.770
Thank you.

11:42.803 --> 11:45.205
I'll leave you to it then.

11:46.406 --> 11:48.876
You okay?

12:12.933 --> 12:15.268
Grandpa?

12:18.471 --> 12:20.740
You're a handsome young man.

12:21.408 --> 12:23.743
What's your name?

12:24.812 --> 12:26.413
Noah.

12:26.947 --> 12:29.482
I'm your grandson.

12:29.516 --> 12:31.318
I don't have a grandson.

12:31.351 --> 12:34.321
Yes. Yes you do.

12:41.962 --> 12:44.197
Yousef you're...

12:46.433 --> 12:49.536
You're not supposed
to be in this house.

12:50.971 --> 12:53.240
It's too dangerous.

12:53.273 --> 12:56.276
I think after 30 years I
actually deserve an explanation.

12:56.309 --> 12:58.946
What is so dangerous
about an old house?

12:58.979 --> 13:03.984
It's not the house,
it's what's in it.

13:09.289 --> 13:10.958
Noah, leave the room.

13:10.991 --> 13:12.826
- Dad
- No, go.

13:19.967 --> 13:23.270
I did what I had
to do to protect you.

13:23.303 --> 13:25.138
Protect me?

13:25.172 --> 13:28.876
You self-righteous piece
of crap, protect me?

13:28.909 --> 13:31.879
I spent 10 years getting my
ass kicked in foster homes

13:31.912 --> 13:34.848
Where was your protection then?

13:35.148 --> 13:38.485
It was for your own good.

13:39.887 --> 13:44.958
Now, please leave.

13:46.093 --> 13:49.396
Before it's too late.

13:51.364 --> 13:55.602
I know you're not an
observant man anymore.

13:58.105 --> 14:02.242
But promise me you will
never lose your faith,

14:02.275 --> 14:04.411
Especially in me.

14:04.945 --> 14:07.380
That's easy.

14:07.414 --> 14:10.450
I never had it to begin with.

14:43.583 --> 14:46.219
Games on in 15,
babe, in and out.

14:50.590 --> 14:52.926
Geez, what's their problem?

14:52.960 --> 14:55.262
You'd think somebody died.

15:00.233 --> 15:02.936
Please behave yourself, Jeff.

15:03.170 --> 15:04.437
What's in it for me?

15:04.471 --> 15:06.239
What do you mean?

15:06.273 --> 15:09.542
We haven't done it in forever.

15:09.576 --> 15:12.079
I wonder why that is.

15:15.615 --> 15:18.551
Oh wow, Beverly Morgan.

15:18.585 --> 15:20.320
You look amazing.

15:20.353 --> 15:22.990
You don't look
half bad yourself.

15:24.657 --> 15:28.128
I am so sorry for
your loss, Yossi.

15:28.161 --> 15:29.396
Thank you,

15:29.429 --> 15:31.631
And it's Joe now.

15:32.499 --> 15:35.435
Joe. Okay.

15:40.040 --> 15:42.509
Hi, Noah Barnett,
at your service.

15:42.542 --> 15:44.978
Chloe.

15:45.378 --> 15:47.647
I'm sorry for your loss.

15:50.117 --> 15:52.085
You must have made this.

15:52.119 --> 15:53.253
Why?

15:53.286 --> 15:55.455
Because it smells heavenly

15:55.488 --> 15:57.991
Can I go now?

15:59.159 --> 16:01.161
I have some flowers for ya.

16:01.194 --> 16:03.063
Uh,

16:03.096 --> 16:04.364
Sorry about your dad, man.

16:04.397 --> 16:06.533
He was a weird old dude.

16:06.566 --> 16:10.137
Yeah. Yeah I should
probably get rid of these.

16:10.170 --> 16:12.505
I just paid 35.99 for those.

16:12.539 --> 16:14.374
You just going to chuck them?

16:14.407 --> 16:17.210
No, in the Jewish tradition
we don't believe in flowers

16:17.244 --> 16:19.412
For mourning, so that's why

16:23.050 --> 16:24.517
You know what, thank you.

16:24.551 --> 16:26.153
These are great.

16:26.186 --> 16:29.389
I'll go put these in water.

16:31.591 --> 16:33.093
Noah?

16:33.126 --> 16:34.327
Yep.

16:34.361 --> 16:36.729
They're not even real.

16:42.835 --> 16:45.405
This sucks.

16:52.079 --> 16:55.182
Joe, I'm so sorry.

16:55.215 --> 16:57.717
Non-Hodgkin's
lymphoma, that's rough.

16:57.750 --> 17:00.387
Yeah it was.

17:00.420 --> 17:02.389
Especially on Noah.

17:02.422 --> 17:06.425
Towards the end, seeing
his mother like that,

17:06.459 --> 17:09.396
Knowing there was nothing
he could do to help.

17:12.165 --> 17:15.268
It really did a
number on both of us.

17:16.303 --> 17:19.506
I know exactly how you feel.

17:19.539 --> 17:24.544
We lost Chloe's dad, my husband,

17:25.244 --> 17:27.214
To colon cancer three years ago.

17:27.247 --> 17:29.449
I'm so sorry.

17:29.482 --> 17:31.551
Thanks.

17:36.389 --> 17:38.391
Let's talk about something,

17:38.425 --> 17:40.093
A little less depressing.

17:40.127 --> 17:42.462
I think that's a great idea.

17:44.264 --> 17:47.167
So Jeff, huh?

17:48.168 --> 17:50.570
Okay, good subject.

18:17.164 --> 18:19.632
Hey, remember when
we were kids your dad

18:19.666 --> 18:23.270
Wouldn't let us be in the
same room alone together?

18:23.636 --> 18:25.438
Oh, the good old days.

18:25.472 --> 18:27.507
We're all grown up now though.

18:27.540 --> 18:29.242
Yes we are.

18:29.276 --> 18:31.611
You were really cute
back then though.

18:31.644 --> 18:34.381
Your glasses, your little curls.

18:35.682 --> 18:37.350
What happened?

18:37.384 --> 18:39.186
Well I don't have
the glasses anymore

18:39.219 --> 18:41.821
And my little curls
are now big curls.

18:41.854 --> 18:46.259
I have much bigger curls
than what I had before.

19:25.365 --> 19:28.601
(Suspenseful music)

19:44.251 --> 19:46.519
So I know you and
Noah have to get back,

19:46.553 --> 19:48.421
But, we're actually
going to a cabin

19:48.455 --> 19:51.424
On Friday if you'd
like to join us.

19:51.458 --> 19:52.992
Oh.

19:53.025 --> 19:56.363
That sounds really
cool, but I think um

19:56.396 --> 19:59.366
There's just a million
things to do around here

19:59.399 --> 20:01.534
You know, and Noah
has school on Monday,

20:01.568 --> 20:04.203
So I think we're just
going to sit this one out.

20:04.604 --> 20:07.240
Maybe next time.

20:17.450 --> 20:20.353
(Thud on wall)

20:29.796 --> 20:32.599
(Pounding)

20:34.066 --> 20:35.402
Noah?

20:35.435 --> 20:37.370
What was that?

20:37.737 --> 20:40.273
Yeah dad.

20:45.912 --> 20:49.616
(Scary music)

21:01.661 --> 21:03.896
Thanks.

21:03.930 --> 21:06.065
Anytime.

21:06.098 --> 21:07.934
It's good to have you back.

21:12.939 --> 21:15.442
If you change your
mind, let me know.

21:15.475 --> 21:17.377
I will.

21:33.726 --> 21:38.731
Ouija, or spirit
board, predates to
China around 1100 A.D.

21:40.500 --> 21:42.769
People commonly use
the board as a way

21:42.802 --> 21:45.505
To contact the dead.

21:47.039 --> 21:51.077
Yeah. I mean what's the
worst that could happen?

21:52.011 --> 21:55.515
Okay board, let's see
what you have to say.

22:19.906 --> 22:24.544
I'm looking for my
mother, Jennifer Barnett.

22:27.580 --> 22:30.116
Mom are you there?

22:31.784 --> 22:33.953
Hello?

22:34.554 --> 22:36.756
Anyone there?

22:36.789 --> 22:38.525
Mom?

22:38.558 --> 22:40.493
Grandpa?

22:40.527 --> 22:42.629
Whoopi?

22:47.033 --> 22:49.402
(Voices)

22:54.941 --> 22:57.944
I knew this thing was bullshit.

23:08.621 --> 23:11.624
(Voices)

23:20.500 --> 23:22.902
(Scary music)

23:39.085 --> 23:41.554
Hello?

24:03.976 --> 24:06.513
What the?

24:14.854 --> 24:18.457
One. Never play alone.

24:19.559 --> 24:22.529
Two. Never let planchette
count down through

24:22.562 --> 24:25.632
The numbers or backwards
through the alphabet.

24:26.999 --> 24:30.537
Three. Never mention God.

24:31.070 --> 24:34.240
Four. Always say goodbye.

24:48.555 --> 24:50.690
I mean, one out
of four ain't bad.

25:13.646 --> 25:15.548
(Door slams)

25:49.682 --> 25:52.284
Hey Dad, does
grandpa have a cat?

25:52.318 --> 25:54.587
I don't think so,
he was allergic.

25:54.621 --> 25:55.888
Why?

25:55.922 --> 25:57.790
No reason.

26:03.663 --> 26:06.599
So, this is it.

26:07.667 --> 26:09.235
Yep.

26:09.268 --> 26:10.637
Look, if you change your mind

26:10.670 --> 26:13.606
Here is the address
to the cabin.

26:13.640 --> 26:16.375
Cell service can be a little
shoddy so just show up, okay?

26:16.408 --> 26:17.644
Okay.

26:17.677 --> 26:19.211
Come on, babe!

26:19.245 --> 26:20.780
We're late for Jeff-town!

26:20.813 --> 26:23.182
Population beers and burgers!

26:26.953 --> 26:29.255
Take care of yourself, Yossi.

26:30.256 --> 26:31.791
Joe.

26:31.824 --> 26:33.826
Sorry, old habits.

26:33.860 --> 26:35.695
Bye, Noah.

26:39.799 --> 26:42.702
So, cabin?

26:42.735 --> 26:44.637
No.

26:46.205 --> 26:49.141
(Upbeat music)

27:04.824 --> 27:07.660
[Jeff] And you make
great sandwiches too.

27:07.694 --> 27:10.663
What do you do?

27:10.997 --> 27:14.266
What do you contribute
to the household?

27:14.300 --> 27:16.703
You drink beer and
you watch football.

27:16.736 --> 27:17.837
And I cook steaks.

27:17.870 --> 27:19.205
Occasionally.

27:19.238 --> 27:21.407
Only when I make you.

27:21.874 --> 27:24.043
Who does the rest of the stuff?

27:24.076 --> 27:26.713
Who fixed the sink the
other day when it got clogged?

27:29.315 --> 27:31.684
What?

27:31.718 --> 27:33.720
Nothing.

27:34.787 --> 27:36.723
We're not going to the cabin.

27:36.756 --> 27:38.925
Fine.

27:43.730 --> 27:45.397
You always said that
grandpa never took you

27:45.431 --> 27:48.267
Anywhere or did anything cool.

27:48.500 --> 27:49.736
I mean it's not like
you're forcing me

27:49.769 --> 27:51.370
To leave home like he did,

27:51.403 --> 27:53.773
But I am going to college.

27:53.806 --> 27:56.375
Don't you want to have
some fun before I go?

28:02.782 --> 28:03.750
What are you doing?

28:03.783 --> 28:05.051
This isn't our exit.

28:05.084 --> 28:06.085
I know.

28:06.118 --> 28:07.887
I'm just proving that I'm cool.

28:07.920 --> 28:10.056
It's not cool if you
say you're cool dad.

28:10.089 --> 28:11.758
Okay.

28:11.791 --> 28:12.725
Well how about
this, I will promise

28:12.759 --> 28:14.426
Not to tell anyone the
only reason you want to

28:14.460 --> 28:17.797
Go to the cabin is so you
can hang out with Chloe.

28:17.830 --> 28:19.431
Have I mentioned you're
the coolest dad ever?

28:19.465 --> 28:22.134
It's not cool to mention it.

28:56.135 --> 28:58.304
Hi guys, sorry,
you just caught me

28:58.337 --> 29:01.040
At the end of my
sun salutations,

29:01.073 --> 29:04.877
I'm working on my
yogi certificate.

29:04.911 --> 29:07.079
You must be Beverly.

29:07.113 --> 29:08.414
Nice to meet you.

29:08.447 --> 29:11.283
Jeff. Hi Chloe.

29:12.518 --> 29:14.453
Teenagers.

29:14.486 --> 29:16.322
Well, make yourselves at home.

29:16.355 --> 29:18.324
The door to the
main house is open,

29:18.357 --> 29:20.426
I'm just going to shower up and

29:20.459 --> 29:21.994
I'll show you guys around.

29:22.028 --> 29:24.263
I'll be right down the
way if you need anything.

29:24.296 --> 29:25.264
Thank you

29:25.297 --> 29:27.934
Thank you. So much.

29:27.967 --> 29:29.969
Get the bags.

29:32.038 --> 29:34.807
What's a yogi
anyway though, a bear?

29:35.474 --> 29:38.811
Yep. She steals
picnic baskets.

29:38.845 --> 29:41.513
That's what I thought.

29:41.547 --> 29:43.015
Let's go.

30:14.146 --> 30:17.516
Jesus, this isn't a
cabin, it's a mansion.

30:17.549 --> 30:20.319
It's like Pablo
Escobar's rustic getaway.

30:20.352 --> 30:22.321
Would you uh, watch
your language please?

30:22.354 --> 30:24.891
What? We're Jewish,
I can say Jesus.

30:24.924 --> 30:27.193
All I'm saying is the cabin
is bigger than our house,

30:27.226 --> 30:29.929
And there's probably a bunch
of cocaine hidden in the walls.

30:29.962 --> 30:30.963
Hey!

30:30.997 --> 30:32.865
What do you know about cocaine?

30:32.899 --> 30:34.600
You know, don't, don't tell me.

30:34.633 --> 30:35.467
Hey!

30:35.501 --> 30:36.869
You guys made it!

30:36.903 --> 30:37.603
Yep.

30:37.636 --> 30:38.537
Good to see you.

30:38.570 --> 30:39.505
Welcome.

30:39.538 --> 30:42.174
Yeah he, guilted me
into it on the highway.

30:42.208 --> 30:44.877
Plus I thought it'd be nice
to make some "cool memories"

30:44.911 --> 30:46.412
Before he goes off to school.

30:46.445 --> 30:47.579
That's really nice.

30:47.613 --> 30:49.548
Chloe's inside and...

30:52.451 --> 30:54.186
Jeff's at the market,

30:54.220 --> 30:55.554
So why don't I show you inside?

30:55.587 --> 30:56.889
Sure, yeah.

30:57.189 --> 30:59.125
Jeff's at the market...

31:27.086 --> 31:28.587
Sup dude?

31:28.620 --> 31:30.056
Sup?

31:30.089 --> 31:30.822
Did you guys change your mind?

31:30.856 --> 31:33.059
Yeah. Yeah,
something like that.

31:33.092 --> 31:35.294
How was the market?

31:35.327 --> 31:37.196
Find anything nice?

31:37.229 --> 31:39.298
Oh, you mean Ronnie.

31:39.331 --> 31:42.368
Ronnie she's like
the yogi around here.

31:42.401 --> 31:46.038
Takes care of stuff when
people are around, whatever

31:46.072 --> 31:49.241
Recent divorcee.

31:50.309 --> 31:53.045
On the prowl.

31:53.079 --> 31:55.047
